> At our local taqueria, a carnitas taco (or 5) is one of our go-to orders. After all, who can resist the rich flavor and tender texture of slow-roasted pork? Tonight, we're creating a quick plant-based version that uses carnitas-style seasonings: chili powder, garlic, and cumin, plus tomato paste for umami-packed richness and poblano pepper for smoky notes. It's all stuffed into steamy tortillas with Monterey Jack cheese, pickled onion, tomato, and chipotle-lime crema—basically, everything we crave on taco night and then some.

Wash and dry all produce.

Halve and peel @red onion{1}; very thinly slice one half and finely chop remaining.

Core, deseed, and dice @poblano pepper{1}(deseeded and diced) into ½-inch pieces.

Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced).

Halve @lime{1}; cut one half into wedges.

== Pickled Onion ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{2%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @water{1%tbsp}. Stir until sugar and salt are mostly dissolved.

Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

== Carnitas Filling ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add half the @ground plant-based protein{9%ounce} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer; cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up protein into pieces and continue cooking until browned all over and warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add poblano and chopped onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Return cooked plant-based protein to pan; add @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and half the @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @water{1/4%cup}, bring to a simmer, and cook until reduced and saucy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: If mixture gets too dry, add more splashes of water as needed.

== Chipotle-Lime Crema ==

While filling cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, a squeeze of juice from lime half to taste, and a pinch of @chipotle powder{1%tsp}.

> Add more chipotle powder to taste if you like things spicy.

Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{}; fill with plant-based protein filling, tomato, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, cilantro, pickled onion(drianing first), and crema.

> TIP: Alternatively, you can put everything in individual serving bowls and let everyone assemble their own tacos.

Serve with lime wedges on the side.